_refine_special_details          
;
Thsi data collection was done while the crystal was subjected to 1.7GPa 
of pressure, within a Merrill-Bassett diamond anvil cell, equipped with
Boehler-Almax cut diamonds. The gasket material was tungsten, and the 
pressure medium was DuPont Krytox. 

 Data were refined as a 2-component twin, in order to account for loss
of symmetry in the transition from Pm\=3m to Im\=3, using the following
twin law: TWIN 0 -1 0 -1 0 0 0 0 -1

Hydrogen atoms were not found in the difference map, so were not refined
in the structure. 

N1 & C1 as well as N2 & C2 occur on the shared special positions, and have 
been refined as such, using EXYZ and EADP.  A SADI was employed. 
;
